Text.Value: Careful - she obviously sees your kindness as weakness. Don't let her take advantage.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Addressed to the player/looking at Lae'zel
EditorData.NodeContext: Speaking to the player regarding Lae'zel. Discreetly urging caution.

Text.Value: Fool. No point in showing a mad dog kindness - it'll still bite you in the end.
I would like you to join me.
Join me, then. But I'll be watching you closely.
Has the error of your ways become clear?
A pity, that.
Scowl all you like - you have my answer.
You would sacrifice yourself to ghaik?
The horned ones mentioned a camp. One there - this Zorru - has seen githyanki.
Such tiring mediocrity.
Chk.
Wait at my camp. We can speak there.
Leave.
Come. We find this Zorru. And we ask where he has seen our kin.
I'm dreadfully curious: might one neutralise the tadpole while keeping its powers?
Lunge for her neck.
And the longer we wait, the more it consumes.
There, we will be purified.
I honour our alliance, kin. Let us seek a crèche.
You have made an ally from Crèche K'liir - few know such fortune. Call me Lae'zel.
Consider your hunger. Fresh blood flows beneath that skin...
I thought you already had a cure. With you, right here.
The tadpole hasn't yet scrambled all your senses. Auspicious.
You were careless with your weapon. Let us hope the tadpole has not scrambled all your senses.

EditorData.logicalname: A player attacked LZ in the cage

Text.Value: Very well. But heed my words.
You will join me. We must find a crèche: our people possess the cure for this infection.
My people possess the cure for this infection. I must find a crèche; you will join me.
Half-elf. I suppose the finer details are lost on a creature like you.
I made an offer, and you accepted. Your fantasy is not my burden.
Wait at my camp. We can speak there.
Fine - we can try working together.
Come. We scout the roads and scan the skies for children of Gith. They will lead us to a crèche.
Come. The horned ones mentioned a camp. One there - this Zorru - has seen githyanki.
The horned ones mentioned a camp. One there - this Zorru - has seen githyanki.
An ally from Crèche K'liir - few know such fortune. You will call me Lae'zel.
A crèche must be near. I must interrogate this Zorru. Our very lives depend on it.
You may as well suggest a wyvern bow to worms.
Purificiation it is, then. You and I better find this crèche.
A crèche must be near. We will ask this Zorru where he has seen my kin.
But the longer we wait, the more it consumes.
I welcome our alliance, kin. We will seek out a crèche.
All right - you are welcome to join me.
All right, we journey together. Let's find this crèche.
If you wish to be rid of the tadpole, you must either be purified - or beheaded.
A crèche? Do you mean a hatchery?
And what exactly is a crèche...?
Sigh. I must decline.
You are full up. Dismiss your weakest warrior.
The cure I offer will suffice as thanks.
The horned hunters mentioned a sighting - one among them has seen our kind.
The horned hunters mentioned a sighting - one among them has seen my kind.
Shka'keth!

EditorData.NodeContext: SHKA-keth! Just like it is spelled.

Text.Value: I know my teachings. There are no half measures.
This means a crèche is near.
Locating a crèche would be wise indeed. Where might we find one?
You do not have the authority. Defer to your leader.
Lies. Just get rid of her.

EditorData.NodeContext: Tersely murmured advice. You're not going to trust her, are you?

Text.Value: We seem like a poor match, frankly. Let's go our separate ways.
You're clearly no friend to tieflings. We'll go our separate ways, I think.
We'll go our separate ways, I think.
It is many things. A hatchery, a training grounds, a shelter.
We scout the roads and scan the skies for children of Gith. They will lead us to a crèche. There, we will be purified.
Well?
I will be at your camp. Do not keep me waiting.
A simple 'thank you' wouldn't go amiss.
I'll trust your judgement - but I won't trust her. Not until I've gotten the measure of her.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Sh addresses the player. She glances at Lae'zel on 'this one'

Text.Value: Githyanki protocol is clear: when infected with a ghaik tadpole, we must report to a ghustil for purification.
You've a sharp tongue, elf. Would that your mind proved its equal.

Synopsis: You recruit Lae'zel to the party. She tells you the only path to a cure of the tadpole in your head is to make your way to a githyanki creche - a nursery and training grounds.
